A DataFrame is a two-dimensional, labeled data structure in Pandas, similar to a table in a database or an Excel spreadsheet. 
Common Operations

    Creating a DataFrame → From lists, dictionaries, CSV files, etc.

    Inspecting Data → .info(), .describe(), .head()

    Selecting & Filtering → Indexing, slicing, conditions

    Modifying Data → Adding/removing columns, updating values

    Handling Missing Values → .fillna(), .dropna()

    Aggregating & Grouping → .groupby(), .agg()
